The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Air-India on Friday slashed the economy class fare on the Calcutta-London route. An economy class passenger from Calcutta on flight AI-151 will have to pay Rs 19,500 for a round trip, down from Rs 26,900. The flight operates three days a week ? Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday. The offer, to be effective from January 20 to March 31, can be availed of by passengers flying only on Tuesdays or Thursdays.

 he last date for purchase of ticket under the scheme is February 15. An airline official said ?attractive schemes? for business class passengers would be announced in a week. 

 Shyamal Rudra, a senior health department official and a former superintendent of NRS Medical College and Hospital, and D.K.Jha, deputy superintendent of the hospital, were suspended on Friday on charges of corruption. Both were found prima facie guilty in a probe, a health department official said. 

 Eight extortionists were arrested in Taratola on Friday afternoon. Acting on a tip-off, police raided an abandoned building on Garagacha Road around 1 pm and rounded up the eight. Four were from Bihar. Twenty-seven firearms and six magazines were seized from them. Police said the gang was plotting a major operation.

 A state electricity board official committed suicide by jumping from the ninth floor of Vidyut Bhavan, in Salt Lake, on Friday evening. Pradip Majumdar, 52, was rushed to hospital, where he was pronounced dead. He was a resident of Khardah, on the northern fringes of the city.

 Train services in Eastern Railway?s Sealdah division will be affected on January 22 and January 29. Power and traffic blocks between Baranagar and Dum Dum Junction stations, and between Belghoria and Dum Dum Junction stations will cause the disruptions. The blocks will continue for eight hours, from 10.30 am to 8.30 pm. Officials said 20 local trains will be cancelled and four terminated at Baranagar. A few long-distance trains ? the Varanasi-Sealdah Express, Jammu Tawai-Sealdah Express, Sampark Kranti Express and the New Jalpaiguri-Sealdah Express ? will be diverted via Naihati. The Down Kanchenjungha Express will be controlled en route.

 Somesh Thakur, president of the Bally local committee of the Congress, was run over by a train on Thursday night. Police said the mishap occurred between Bally and Belur stations while Thakur was trying to cross the tracks.

 Subhasish Mallik, 52, a trader, committed suicide by hanging himself from the ceiling of his Kailash Bose Street house, in north Calcutta, on Friday morning. He left behind a note, in which he said huge losses in business had forced him to end his life. The body has been sent for post-mortem.

 Governor Gopal Krishna Gandhi on Friday inaugurated the golden jubilee celebrations of Kalikapur Basanti Devi Girls? Higher Secondary School, in Sonarpur, on the southern fringes of the city. 

 State urban development minister Asok Bhattacharya on Friday unveiled a reservoir for arsenic-free ground water in Mahestala, on the southern fringes of the city. The reservoir?s capacity is 50 gallons. 

